%% Complementary Quality Gates Diagram
%% Shows how different code quality tools work together in a comprehensive
%% quality assurance pipeline
%%
%% Quality Gate Layers:
%% 1. Linters & Type Checkers - Catches syntax errors, type issues
%% 2. AI Code Review - Catches logic bugs, best practices, context issues
%% 3. SAST/SonarQube - Catches known vulnerabilities (CWE/OWASP)
%% 4. Human Architectural Review - Validates system design and business logic
%%
%% This layered approach provides defense-in-depth for code quality
%%
%% Color Legend:
%% - Blue (#3B82F6): Starting point
%% - Purple (#7C3AED): AI-powered quality gate
%% - Green (#10B981): Final deployment

graph TD
    A[Code Change] --> B[Linters & Type Checkers]
    B --> C[AI Code Review]
    C --> D[SAST/SonarQube]
    D --> E[Human Architectural Review]
    E --> F[Merge & Deploy]
    
    B -.->|Catches| B1[Syntax Errors<br/>Type Issues]
    C -.->|Catches| C1[Logic Bugs<br/>Best Practices<br/>Context Issues]
    D -.->|Catches| D1[Known Vulnerabilities<br/>CWE/OWASP]
    E -.->|Validates| E1[System Design<br/>Business Logic]
    
    style A fill:#3B82F6,color:#fff
    style C fill:#7C3AED,color:#fff
    style F fill:#10B981,color:#fff
